text: Struggling to pick up my life againI hope someone in this group could relate to my situation and offer some help  The death of my sister in   and my wife in   prompted me to completely change my seemingly egoistic life and I turned to helping others  I am now realising rather late how I ve ruined my personal finances as a result  I am now trying to pick up my life again but I must meet my immediate needs  I ve got a quit notice on my rented appartment which expires today  My landlady is tired of my excuses  She might relent if I offered a tangible proof that I could meet up my payments or pay my debts to her  If only someone out there could relate and be in a postion to help  I m determined to solve my problems in the long run  I only need a little breathing space from my urgent financial worries  Yes  I have picked up useful tips on this site and others already  like crowdfunding  which I will apply to my long term plans because I really don t want to turn my back from helping others  I view all these financial burderns closing in on me and it scares because I can t imagine myself bouncing back as a homeless person  I live in Germany  Suicide is a permanent solution to a temporary problem  that is why my appeal for help here  I ve been struggling with the suicide thoughts for a while now since I exhausted my search for assistance from among friends and colleagues  None of them takes me seriously or they have their own problems to tackle  Please don t scorn at me or laugh it off  I will provide further details to anyone who genuinely wants to help and I will answer your questions
summary: The death of his sister and wife prompted him to change his life and he turned to helping others. Now he has ruined his personal finances and is struggling to meet his immediate needs. He has a quit notice on his rented apartment which expires today. He lives in Germany. He will provide details to anyone who wants to help him.

text: Question Ok  so here goes  For a long while I just went wild  Drugs  booze  all round poor choices  Never been in any real trouble with the law even though there were numerous occasions where I should have been Now I m clean  I m sober  Trying to build a life  Be a productive member of society  But I m having a seriously hard time getting over some things I ve done in my life  People I ve wronged used abused I m not that person anymore  I don t condone any of my past actions  I don t want that lifestyle  I feel like hope that I ve put that part of my life to rest  I don t ask for much out of life  I just want to be a good father to my daughter  To be a potential husband to my girlfriend  To have a simple calm life  Nothing fancy  just the loves in my life and a home to live life These past few months I just can t seem to shake my past actions  Nothing in the way of getting back into old habits  Just memories and nightmares  So much so that I ve been strongly contemplating suicide  I don t know what to do  I don t know how to bring this up to my partner  I m just a little lost and confused  How do I let go of the hurt that I ve caused myself and others of my past  How do I get over this and continue to grow and work towards my life s goals   Why is it so irritatingly easy to just want to give up and end everything  Why am I like this  I don t want to be the person I was as a young adult  I can t hold on much longer  There s only so much I can take
summary: For a long time I went wild. Now I'm sober and trying to build a life. I want to be a good father to my daughter, a potential husband to his girlfriend and live a simple calm life. He's considering suicide because of his past.
